samples <- read_excel(here("water_quality", "samples.xlsx"), sheet = "raw_data") %>% clean_names() %>%
  select(-nitrate_raw)
control <- filter(samples, type == "control")
# ph
ggplot(filter(samples, type == "sample"), aes(x = site, y = ph)) +
  geom_point(color = "steelblue") +
  geom_hline(yintercept = control$ph, linetype = "dashed", color = "gray") +
  labs(x = "", y = "pH") +
  ylim(0, 14) +
  theme_bw() +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, hjust = 1))

# tds
ggplot(filter(samples, type == "sample"), aes(x = site, y = tds)) +
  geom_point(color = "steelblue") +
  geom_hline(yintercept = control$tds, linetype = "dashed", color = "gray") +
  labs(x = "", y = "TDS (ppm)") +
  ylim(30000, 40000) +
  theme_bw() +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, hjust = 1))

# salinity
ggplot(filter(samples, type == "sample"), aes(x = site, y = salinity)) +
  geom_point(color = "steelblue") +
  geom_hline(yintercept = control$salinity, linetype = "dashed", color = "gray") +
  labs(x = "", y = "Salinity (ppm)") +
  ylim(30000, 40000) +
  theme_bw() +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, hjust = 1))
